# UI Construction

This rule governs how to write UI in a Thunderstorm project. It covers React component structure, SCSS conventions, design token usage, and the integration patterns between them. Treat every item here as non-negotiable.

---

## 1. Component file naming

Every component file has a type-prefix that describes its role in the hierarchy. The prefix determines what the component does, not where it lives.

| Prefix | Role |
|--------|------|
| `Page_` | Full-page owner. Mounts in a route. Owns workspace layout, module-to-state wiring, edit/view mode orchestration. |
| `Manager_` | WorkHub slot component. Receives `WorkHubItem` + `renderArgs`. Composes panels and editors for one domain object. |
| `Editor_` | Focused edit surface for a domain object. Holds `EditableDBItemV3`, tab structure, and save logic. |
| `Renderer_` | Read or edit rendering of a sub-section. May receive an `editable` prop and an `editMode` flag. Not independently routed. |
| `Panel_` | A vertical slice of a workspace (list panel, detail panel). Receives selection state from parent. |
| `Component_` | Self-contained, reusable, feature-complete unit. Has its own internal state. Cross-domain. |
| `Header_` | Bar or title region for an entity view — back nav, title, action buttons. |
| `Dialog_` | Modal content component. Always co-located with its open trigger. |
| `Field_` | Single atomic form field: label + input + validation display, bound to one prop of an editable. |

**Naming pattern:** `[Prefix]_[Domain][SubDomain]` — PascalCase, underscored separator.

```
Manager_DiseaseProfile
Editor_DiseaseProfile
Renderer_PathwayStateEditor
Panel_MultiVarList
Header_PathwayState
Dialog_DuplicatePathway
Field_DiseaseLabel
```

The file name matches the class/function name exactly. The SCSS file has the same base name.

