## 3. Design tokens — always use them, never bypass them

### Colors

**Never write a hex value or rgb() in component SCSS.** Use the `C` namespace from `@app/styles/color`.

```scss
@use '@app/styles/color' as C;

// Correct
color: C.$primary-02;
border-color: C.$secondary-05;
background: C.red(4);

// Wrong — hardcoded values
color: #4f4f4f;
border: 1px solid #e3e9f2;
background: #f6f8fc;
```

Palette functions: `C.red($i)`, `C.gray($i)`, `C.green($i)` etc. where `$i` is 1–7 (1 = lightest, 7 = darkest).

**No local color variables.** Do not define `$font-color: #333` or similar at the top of a component SCSS file. That color belongs in the design system — find or add it there.

### Mixins

Use the `S` namespace from `@nu-art/ts-styles` for all interaction and utility mixins.

```scss
@use '@nu-art/ts-styles' as S;

@include S.mouse-interactive-background(C.$secondary-06, C.$secondary-05);
@include S.mouse-interactive-text(C.$primary-02, #fff);
@include S.color-svg(C.$primary-02);
@include S.mouse-interactive-icon(C.$primary-02);
@include S.text-ellipsis;
@include S.customScrollbar('vertical', true);
```

Do not write raw `&:hover { background: X; } &:active { background: Y; }` chains. The mixin handles hover + active + disabled correctly in one call.

### Inline styles

The only acceptable use of inline `style={{}}` in TSX is for values that come from data — a color stored in the database, a dynamically computed pixel offset. Never use it for design decisions.

```tsx
// Correct — color comes from DB record
<div style={{ background: dpColor.colors[0] }} />

// Wrong — design decision belongs in SCSS
<div style={{ padding: '30px', gap: '10px' }} />
```

