## 5. Layout primitives — always use them

Never write `display: flex; flex-direction: column` or `display: flex; align-items: center` on a raw `<div>`. Use layout primitives from `@nu-art/thunderstorm-frontend`:

| Component | Renders as | Use for |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| `LL_V_L` | `div` flex column, align left | Default vertical stack |
| `LL_V_C` | `div` flex column, align center | Centered column content |
| `LL_H_C` | `div` flex row, align center | Horizontal row, vertically centered |
| `LL_H_T` | `div` flex row, align top | Row where items have different heights |
| `LL_H_B` | `div` flex row, align bottom | Row aligned to bottom |
| `LL_VH_C` | `div` flex, centered both axes | Full-height centered container |
| `Grid` | `div` CSS grid | Any grid layout |

```tsx
// Correct
<LL_H_C className={'h__pathway-state'}>
  <LL_V_L className={'h__pathway-state__info'}>
    <span>{title}</span>
  </LL_V_L>
</LL_H_C>

// Wrong
<div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column' }}>
```

All layout primitives pass `className` and all standard div props through.

