## 6. SCSS file organization

```
MyComponent/
  MyComponent.tsx
  MyComponent.scss       ← always co-located, always same base name
  consts.scss            ← only when siblings share placeholders
  types.ts               ← shared types for this component family
```

**One SCSS file per TSX file.** A component that has no SCSS (pure composition) needs no `.scss` file.

### Import order in SCSS files

```scss
@use '@nu-art/ts-styles' as S;      // 1. Thunderstorm mixins
@use '@app/styles/color' as C;      // 2. Color tokens
@use '@app/styles/km2' as *;        // 3. KM2 design placeholders (if needed)
@use './consts' as *;               // 4. Local component family consts (if exists)
```

**Never use `@import`** — it is deprecated in modern SCSS. Always `@use`.

**Never use wildcard imports (`as *`) for external packages** — only for local `consts.scss` within the same component family where all exported names are known.

