## 8. State management — EditableDBItemV3

**All DB entity editing goes through `EditableDBItemV3`.** Never mutate a cached entity directly. This is covered in detail in [editable-item-pattern.mdc](editable-item-pattern.mdc) — this section covers how to chain it correctly in this codebase.

Standard pattern for an editor that auto-saves:

```tsx
private buildEditable(diseaseProfileId: UniqueId): EditableDBItemV3<DBProto_DiseaseProfile> {
  const diseaseProfile = ModuleFE_DiseaseProfile.cache.unique(diseaseProfileId);
  if (!diseaseProfile)
    throw new BadImplementationException(`Could not find disease profile for id ${diseaseProfileId}`);

  return new EditableDBItemV3(diseaseProfile, ModuleFE_DiseaseProfile)
    .setAutoSave(true)
    .setDebounceTimeout(200)
    .setOnChanged(async () => this.forceUpdate())
    .setOnSaveCompleted(() => this.forceUpdate());
}
```

Standard pattern for an editor with explicit save button:

```tsx
private buildEditable(item: DB_SomeEntity): EditableDBItemV3<DBProto_SomeEntity> {
  return new EditableDBItemV3(item, ModuleFE_SomeEntity)
    .setAutoSave(false);
}

private onSave = async () => {
  if (!this.canSave()) return;
  await this.state.editable.save();
  this.props.functions.deselectItem();
};
```

