## 9. Edit/view mode pattern

### Full mode switch via Component_SwitchView

Use `Component_SwitchView` when a component has a complete view mode and a complete edit mode with different layouts:

```tsx
private pathwayStateEditor(editable: EditableItem<UI_PathwayState>) {
  return <Component_SwitchView
    mode={this.getModeKey()}
    modes={[
      {
        key: viewKey,
        renderer: () => <Renderer_PathwayStateDetails editable={editable} toggleEdit={this.toggleEdit} />
      },
      {
        key: editKey,
        permissionKey: this.permissionKey_Edit,
        renderer: () => <Renderer_PathwayStateEditor editable={editable} toggleMode={this.toggleEdit} />
      }
    ]}
  />;
}
```

### Field-level edit/view via disabled prop

When the component is structurally the same in both modes (same layout, same fields) and only field interactivity changes, pass `editMode` down and use the KM2 disabled design:

```tsx
<TS_Input
  type={'text'}
  value={editable.item.label}
  onChange={this.onLabelChange}
  disabled={!props.editMode}
/>
```

`%KM2Design_Input` handles the disabled visual automatically: transparent border, no cursor, plain text display. Do not add custom disabled styling — the design system handles it.

