## 10. Tabs — typed constants, not string arrays

Tab UIDs and option lists must be typed constants or string literal union types. Never use raw string arrays.

```tsx
// Correct
type ProfileTab = 'general' | 'scores' | 'epidemiology' | 'prognosis' | 'references';

const tabs: Tab[] = [
  { uid: 'general',       title: 'General',       content: () => <Editor_DiseaseProfile_General ... /> },
  { uid: 'scores',        title: 'Scores',        content: () => <Editor_DiseaseProfile_Scores ... /> },
  { uid: 'epidemiology',  title: 'Epidemiology',  content: () => <Editor_DiseaseProfile_Epidemiology ... /> },
];

// Wrong
const varOptions = ['Overview', 'Disease Info', 'Snomed Info', ...];
```

