## 12. Spotting old code — what to flag and why

When reviewing or refactoring existing code, the following are immediate signals of pre-standard patterns that should be migrated:

| Signal in code | What it tells you | What it should be |
|----------------|------------------|-------------------|
| `#manager__disease-profile { }` | ID-root SCSS | `.m__disease-profile { }` |
| `$font-color: #333;` at top of SCSS | Local design token | Use `C.$primary-02` or appropriate C token |
| `.manager__disease-profile__disease-variable-data__header__title` | Over-deep flat BEM | SCSS nesting with shorter element names |
| `display: flex; align-items: center` on div | Missing layout primitive | `<LL_H_C>` |
| `style={{ padding: '30px', gap: '10px' }}` | Inline design | SCSS class |
| `color: #4f4f4f` | Hardcoded color | `C.$primary-02` or `C.gray(5)` |
| `const varOptions = ['Overview', 'Disease Info', ...]` | Untyped string list | Typed string literal union |
| `@import` in SCSS | Old SCSS import | `@use` with namespace |
| `EditableDBItemV2` or raw `module.cache.unique()` + setState | Old entity editing | `EditableDBItemV3` with `.setAutoSave().setOnChanged()` |
| `if (!editMode) return <viewJSX>; else return <editJSX>` | Ad-hoc mode branching | `Component_SwitchView` or `disabled={!editMode}` |

